title: Google : global corporate demography 2014 - 2019 , by gender
summary: This is a multi-line chart with 2 lines representing Female, and Male. The y axis denotes Share of employees and the x axis denotes Year.
Overall Female, and Male are roughly constant,  throughout the Year
The lines ordered according to average values of Share of employees in descending order is: 1. Male, and lastly, 2. Female.
Throughout the period, Male generally had the highest Share of employees relative to others with an average of 69.15, and it reached its maximum at 2014, 2015, and 2016 with a value of 69.4.
Female mostly had the least Share of employees with a mean value of 30.85, which peaked at 2019 with a value of 31.6.
